programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dark Signs, Part 4

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Supersensory Shakedown

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Digging Deeper, Part 1
programme.desc: With Lazar's creepy clowns about to crack Crow's defense, Crow hatches a plan to lull his opponent into a false sense of security so that his feathered friends can swoop in and swipe the last of Lazar's life points.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Digging Deeper, Part 2

programme.title: Dragon
programme.desc: A princess must recruit the most brave and powerful swordsmen in the land with the sole purpose of vanquishing the dark wizard who terrorizes the kingdom with a giant, menacing dragon.

programme.title: Elvis Lives!
programme.desc: Elvis, bored and past his prime, is delighted at the opportunity to work as a secret agent for the FBI. But when he gets in too deep with the mob and his daughter and father are threatened, he fakes his own death.

programme.title: Merlin and the War of the Dragons
programme.desc: An army of dragons invade the crippled English countryside and the apprentice wizard Merlin must confront the fire-breathing beasts.

programme.title: Titanic II
programme.desc: On the 100th anniversary of the original voyage, a luxury liner follows the path of its namesake. But when a tsunami hurls an ice berg into the new ship's path, the passengers and crew must fight to avoid a similar fate.

programme.title: Trolland
programme.desc: Fenn the Troll hates the Troll pastime of pranking, and is teased so much for it that he runs away. But when a long-suffering park ranger starts capturing the other Trolls, it’s up to Fenn to rescue his family and friends - without pranking.

programme.title: In the Name of Ben-Hur
programme.desc: A young gladiator enslaved in the Roman arena in 171 A.D. escapes by chariot towards the freedom of Hadrian's Wall. Fighting centurions and mercenaries along the way, he becomes a folk hero for all those struggling to fight Roman oppression.

programme.title: Meteor Apocalypse
programme.desc: In this End Times thriller, a gigantic meteor enters Earth's orbit and begins to disintegrate, showering the planet in poisonous debris.

programme.title: Oceans Rising
programme.desc: A scientist builds a massive ark after his warnings of an Earth-destroying flood are ignored. But when it’s evident the disaster will occur, those who maligned the scientist now turn to him in desperation, boarding the ark and seeking his answers.

programme.title: The Bell Witch Haunting
programme.desc: The Robertson County Sheriff's Department released found footage of what was thought at first to be a murder suicide, is now believed to be the return of a centuries old demon responsible for America's most famous paranormal event.

programme.title: Halloween Night
programme.desc: Halloween Night, 1982, an inmate of a maximum security facility escapes after murdering two guards. Upon returning to the house where he was born, he goes on a killing spree that will make him Southern California's greatest mass murderer.

programme.title: 666: The Child
programme.desc: After a plane crash where a boy is the only survivor, a childless couple adopts him and soon discovers he is something very powerful and very dark. This small boy is the Beast, and with him he carries the Beginning of the End.

programme.title: Monster
programme.desc: After a massive earthquake in Tokyo, two American filmmakers document the true cause of the destruction.

programme.title: Hansel VS Gretel
programme.desc: Trapped under a dark spell, Gretel assembles a coven of witches that starts to terrorize the town until Hansel gains the courage to fight his sister and the sinister forces that control her.

programme.title: Meteor Apocalypse
programme.desc: In this End Times thriller, a gigantic meteor enters Earth's orbit and begins to disintegrate, showering the planet in poisonous debris.

programme.title: 2012: Doomsday
programme.desc: Four strangers on a journey of faith are drawn to a temple in the heart of Mexico on December 21, 2012. For the Mayans it is the last recorded day. For NASA scientists it is a cataclysmic polar shift. For the rest of us, it is Doomsday.

programme.title: 2010: Moby Dick
programme.desc: A modern adaptation of the classic novel of the captain of a high tech submarine and his obsessive quest to destroy the enormous prehistoric whale that maimed him.

programme.title: Flight World War II
programme.desc: Caught in a battle between Allied and German Forces, a modern day 757 mysteriously travels back in time to 1940. In their desperation to return home safely, the plane's passengers manage to turn the tide that wins the war in Europe.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Man with a Cane
programme.desc: The team head to Bolton and investigate the Old Three Crowns. Haunted by the spirit of a very angry man with a deadly cane and an upset, young, ghostly girl, will they uncover why the girl is so upset? And could they encounter the angry spirit man?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: I Hear a Baby Crying
programme.desc: The team investigate the Market Hotel in Bolton. Believed to be haunted by the lost soul of a previous landlord and a guest who likes to make herself known. They make contact with spirits from the other side and witness first hand paranormal activity.

programme.title: Halloween Special
programme.desc: Join Bex, Sean and the team as they investigate The Wellington Hotel for Halloween. Based in Halewood, this public inn has more haunting inside of its walls than the spirits behind the bar.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The House of The Devil
programme.desc: The island of Gran Canaria houses some of the most haunted buildings in the world and tonight the team fly to the island and investigate claims of satanic worship and paranormal activity in a house that is believed to have been built by the Devil himself.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: House of Fear
programme.desc: Located in Gran Canaria, there is one house that locals refuse to enter and that is, The House of Fear. Ghostly shadows, loud banging and demonic voices have all been reported here and the Ghost Dimension team will investigate these claims tonight.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension investigate ruins of The Orangery in Merseyside and claims that the ghost of a grey lady is haunting the location. They capture some of the most compelling paranormal evidence they have ever encountered.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: What Haunts Inside?
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension is an exciting paranormal show that takes investigations to a whole new level.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Halloween Special (2019)
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension is an exciting paranormal show that takes investigations to a whole new level.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: The Curse Of The Pendle Witches - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads deep into the Pendle Hills in search of the Pendle Witches that went to trial in 1612 and were hung for witchcraft. The investigation takes an unexpected twist with a stop at the New Inn, Pendles most haunted pub.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: The Curse Of The Pendle Witches - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of Pendle Hill and ventures even deeper into the hills. The night takes an unexpected turn with a dramatic ending, which he believes was caused by the witches.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Shadow Menace Haunting Morley Market - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to the town of Morley to investigate the infamous Morley Market. A place once bustling with people from years gone by, it is now haunted by shadow figures, and they appear to want to make themselves known.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Shadow Menace Haunting Morley Market - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues the investigation at Morley Market and appears to be followed by a spirit person that wants to touch him and distract him from investigating certain parts of the main hall. Will he uncover who this spirit is?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Horror at Sandhole Cottage - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean returns to his former, haunted home. No tenant has ever been able to stay the full term. Sean wants to seek out the spirits once and for all, to finally find out what is haunting his former home.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Horror at Sandhole Cottage - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of Sandhole Cottage and appears to be in direct contact with the spirits that haunted any tenants that came to live there. Will he finally get them to rest?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Opening The Book at Leeds Library - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean delves deep and opens a new chapter for the Ghost Dimension Flying Solo series as he investigates Leeds Library, to uncover what is haunting and frightening the staff that work here.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Closing The Book at Leeds Library - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation at Leeds Library and attempts to communicate with a spirit known by the name of Sternberg. Will his investigation have a happy ending?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Secret Spirits at The Old Market Tavern - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Altrincham, Greater Manchester to investigate The Old Market Tavern. Once used as a coaching inn and a court house, many spirits still lurk here and Sean captures one of the most clearest EVP's ever.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Secret Spirits at The Old Market Tavern - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his paranormal investigation at The Old Market Tavern and he appears to have attracted the attention of spirit that launches a physical attack on him. Will he survive the night?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo
programme.desc: Sean heads to Astley Green to the infamous Astley Green Colliery Museum. So many reports of paranormal activity have been confirmed at the mine, from lost miners to tormented souls.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Digging Deep Astley Green Colliery Museum - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation into Astley Green Colliery Museum and attempts to make further contact with the souls and spirits who have lost their lives there. Will he succeed?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Historic Hauntings of Whittington Castle - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Oswestry to investigate claims of hauntings at a castle thousands of years old, and believed to be haunted by an angry judge. Will any of the souls that departed here come out to play?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Historic Hauntings of Whittington Castle - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of the castle and attempts to make contact with the spirit world. It appears he is not alone.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: 14 Ghosts of The Bate Hall
programme.desc: Sean heads to Macclesfield, Cheshire to investigate a building said to be haunted by 14 ghosts and also the lost soul of a witch. With so many spirits in one of the oldest public houses in the UK, will any of the ghosts join him tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Haunting of The Sad Cavalier at The Ring O Bells - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Middleton, Manchester to investigate claims that a sad cavalier named Edward is haunting this location. Ring O Bells has also been used for druid rituals. Will he be able to summon any spirits tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Haunting of The Sad Cavalier at The Ring O Bells - Part 2
programme.desc: As Sean continues his investigation at The Ring O Bells pub, he finds that out that there is more haunting this location, than just the spirits lurking behind the bar.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo
programme.desc: Sean investigates one of the UK's most haunted pubs, with is very own dungeon. Haunted by multiple spirits, it appears to be very active and Sean is not prepared for what happens to Paul.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Poltergeist Haunting The Station Hotel - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Ashton-Under-Lyne to investigate poltergeist activity claims in a local pub. It's believed that it's not just the locals that return to haunt here. Sean comes face to face with the activity in a night he will never forget.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Poltergeist Haunting The Station Hotel - Part 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation at The Station Hotel and it appears his presence is not welcomed by the spirits. This is one experience of the paranormal that leaves a mark in Sean's memory forever.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Haunted escape room at Moviescape - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to a haunted escape room attraction and although the sets are dressed to scare, something more sinister seems to be lurking here. Will Sean escape unscathed tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of the escape rooms and investigates the haunted bible and radio. Prepare for a fright when Sean and Paul join forces and witness paranormal activity firsthand.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Spirits in command at Welkin Mill
programme.desc: Sean heads into Stockport, Greater Manchester and travels to Welkin Mill. He investigates claims of paranormal activity which also appear to be linked to his previous investigation of Moviescape.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Will it All Go Pear Shaped at Pear Mill? - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Stockport to investigate a haunted mill, which has a lift with a mind all of its own. Will any of the ghosts haunting the mill join him on the investigation tonight or will it all go pear shaped?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Will it All Go Pear Shaped at Pear Mill? - Pear 2
programme.desc: Sean continues his investigation of the mill and is attacked by a spirit. Jane joins the investigation with surprising results. Will it have a happy ending?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Forgotten Souls of Errwood Hall
programme.desc: Sean heads to the Errwood Hall ruins in the Goyt Valley. It is said to be haunted by 3 spirits, and that it has its very own time slip. The investigation does not disappoint and although the hall is gone, the spirits remain.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Escape the Escape Room - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean enters one of the UK's most haunted escape rooms and it appears that he is not the only one trying to escape. Will the spirits play games with him tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Escape the Escape Room - Part 2
programme.desc: The investigation continues at the escape room and a certain spirit attempts to tug at Sean's clothing. Will he finally survive the escape room?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Lock Keepers Haunting at Lock 91
programme.desc: Sean heads to Manchester to investigate a lock keeper's cottage that was built in 1804. It appears that the spirits are still watching over the building and terrifying its customers.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Flying Solo: Lights Out at Abbey House Museum - Part 1
programme.desc: Sean heads to Leeds and investigates Abbey House Museum among a maze of Victorian streets and shops. Who will he bump into tonight and what secrets does this location hold?

programme.title: Choking Man
programme.desc: The social anxiety of a morbidly shy Ecuadorian dishwasher working in a Queens diner provides the psychological engine that powers this blend of drama and magical realism. Starring: Aaron Paul, Octavio Gómez Berríos, Eugenia Yuan, Mandy Patinkin.

programme.title: Deconstructing Harry
programme.desc: Suffering from writer's block and eagerly awaiting his writing award, Harry Block remembers events from his past and scenes from his best-selling books as characters, real and fictional, come back to haunt him. Starring: Woody Allen, Judy Davis.

programme.title: Bernie
programme.desc: In small-town Texas, an affable mortician strikes up a friendship with a wealthy widow, though when she starts to become controlling, he goes to great lengths to separate himself from her grasp. Starring: Jack Black, Shirley MacLaine, Matthew McConaughey.

programme.title: Gracie
programme.desc: A teenager faces an uphill battle when she fights to give women the opportunity to play competitive soccer.

programme.title: Rise Of The Chupacabras
programme.desc: A treasure map leads a group of unsuspecting townsfolk to the lair of vampire-like creatures known as the Chupacabras.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Obsession
programme.desc: Deciphering what causes minds to corkscrew out of control is the complex work of the criminal profiler. Obsessions can take many forms: beauty, devotion, ego and power.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Hearts of Stone
programme.desc: Deadly Women are not always the ones you expect. They are not the strangers lurking in the dark, they are a young mother, a supportive wife and a grandmother - all killers. Behind their loving masquerade lies a wake of family horror and pain.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Greed
programme.desc: Known as “black widows,” these women kill their spouses, lovers and children for profit. Murder for them becomes a business. Their trade is murder. Their profit? Blood money.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Crimes of revenge are usually single acts of passion. A brew of hatred and restitution boils over in a manic moment of fury. Once caught, revenge killers usually display remorse and atonement.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: No one doubts a woman’s capacity to love, but sometimes lust can turn lethal. In the ultimate fatal attraction, "Deadly Women" looks at cases of murder driven by obsessive love.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A rifle in a shopping mall, a syringe of potassium chloride and a syringe of insulin, each in the hands of a mentally disturbed woman, lead to the tragic end of many lives.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Judi Buenoano secretly murdered lovers to claim on insurance policies whilst nurse Genene Jones secretly killed at least 46 infants left in her care between 1980 and 1982.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Nurse Beverley Allitt overdosed multiple infants, Stella Nickell poisoned medicine capsules in stores and Kathleen Follbigg killed four of her own children.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Women are more often prey than predators, but the exceptions are deadly women indeed. In this episode, we’ll discover what drove these deadly women to prey on the unsuspecting.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women would stop at nothing to get their hands on the cash they needed. From husbands to strangers to other people’s babies, they spilt blood for money.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Behind lace-curtained windows and beneath sensible haircuts lurked evil. Appearances were deceptive. We did not notice these female killers walking by. These women wore a mask of sanity.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women burn madly with jealousy, an anger so deep they’ll kill to satisfy it. What makes them turn from “green with envy” to “lethal with jealousy?" Find out as we explore their hearts of darkness.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: In some cases, the transformation from everyday woman to brutal killer is activated by a man. A boyfriend or husband can become the focus of a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Psychopathic killers lurk in society, mostly acting alone. Sometimes fate brings them into contact with another person who shares their cold power to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: We want to believe that all women would give their lives to protect their children. But there are horrifying cases when a mother will turn against her natural instinct and kill her own flesh and blood.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The mind of a female killer is shaped by a complex cocktail of influences. Do people become that way, driven by horrendous events in their lives? Or are some killers born bad?

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Blood ties are strong ties, sometimes strong enough to pull a person into a murderous conspiracy. When a family member wields his or her power, the result can be death.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The path towards revenge can sometimes lead to murder. It can be quick, fiery and violent. It can also be a dish served cold, the product of a calm, calculated plot.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: While their sisters chose a life of sensible, suburban motherhood, these deadly women chose a life of crime. They lived with the thrills, the danger and the deadly consequences of being outlaws.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Sometimes, when a man and a woman unite, a terrible urge for destruction can awaken in them both. Happy couples become deadly teams, intent on one goal: murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women never get their hands dirty: no blood touched them because they manipulate others to kill for them...but they didn't get away.

programme.title: Deadly Women

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dishonored
programme.desc: Shirley Russell was determined enough to reach the rank of Captain in the United States Marine Corps. When this officer turned up missing, her colleagues refused to believe she had gone AWOL. It was unclear whether Captain Shirley Russell was alive.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Millionaire Murder
programme.desc: A businessman went to Florida to make one last deal before he retired-he never returned home to his millions. Authorities examined who was closest to him and who stood to gain from his disappearance. But this time conventional rules didn't apply.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Business
programme.desc: Many escape the poverty of India to start new lives in the United States. One turned the American dream into a nightmare. People started turning up dead in New York's Indian community-authorities struggled to link fraud and murder to a powerful man.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Temple of Fear
programme.desc: In Miami, the discovery of a mutilated body sent investigators on the trail of a deadly cult. But agents found a wall of silence around the cult's members. Potential witnesses, terrified of reprisals, refused to talk.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Silent Strike
programme.desc: Money may not be the root of all evil, but for some men, a million dollars is enough to justify murder. Even men sworn to uphold the law can sometimes be tempted.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Stranger
programme.desc: The body of a young woman found burned in a truck launched a manhunt to find her killer. When more bodies began to turn up across the country, the FBI believed the cases were linked. Investigators had a suspect. They just couldn't find him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Backstage Murder
programme.desc: In the 1980's, two partners created a nightclub that would bring them wealth and international fame. The male strip club phenomenon promised female patrons fun and excitement. But the bright lights hid a dark side.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Under Fire
programme.desc: A series of armored car heists and bloody shoot-outs shocked law enforcement. The brutal violence of the crimes suggested a motive more complex than greed. When the robbers started targeting police, the FBI took charge.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Manhunt
programme.desc: A killer was on the loose in one of America's most popular tourist destinations. Armed and desperate, he evaded law enforcement at every turn. As the Fourth of July weekend quickly approached, thousands of people became potential targets.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Target
programme.desc: Over a thousand hunting accidents are reported in the United States each year. Fewer than ten percent of them are fatal. But when one hunter's death seemed suspicious, the FBI was called in to investigate.

programme.title: The FBI Files: No Remorse
programme.desc: A burning body in a dark alley shed light on a cold-blooded killer. His partners in crime would tell the story, if they lived. In the underworld of the drug trade, even a childhood friend can quickly become an enemy.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The C-11 Squad
programme.desc: New York City is not stranger to gang violence. But when a 12-year-old child was kidnapped, the gangs had crossed a line. Law enforcement raced to find the missing boy before it was too late.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Polly Klaas: Kidnapped
programme.desc: On October 1, 1993, a stranger abducted 12-year-old Polly Klaas during a slumber party in her home.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Above the Law
programme.desc: California Highway Patrolman George Gwaltney discovered the body of 23-year-old Robin Bishop near her car on a remote desert highway.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Human Prey
programme.desc: Thomas Dillon killed five outdoorsmen at random over a period of three years in rural southern Ohio. After a tip led the FBI to the murder weapon, ballistic testing made a match.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Death in Alaska
programme.desc: The day began like any other for Cheryl and Paul Chapman, until the silence of a peaceful Sunday morning was shattered with a phone call.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Paradise
programme.desc: It should have been Shangri-La, but when bad blood developed, piracy took over and the only law was the law of the jungle.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Crazy Don
programme.desc: To the FBI, he was believed to be the boss of New York's most powerful mafia organization: the Genovese crime family. Was Gigante crazy or was his behavior a shrewd attempt to disguise his position as a ruthless mafia boss?

programme.title: The FBI Files: Killing Spree
programme.desc: In 1984, in South Florida, a rapist and murderer was on the loose. The killer was a ruthless and terrifying predator, the newest member of an infamous group known as serial killers.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Melissa Brannen: Missing
programme.desc: In 1989, residents of a close-knit apartment community in Virginia gathered for a holiday celebration. For Tammy Brannen and five-year-old daughter Melissa, Christmas was always a special time. Then, without warning, the little girl was gone.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Unabomber
programme.desc: For nearly two decades a mathematical genius with delusions of single-handedly destroying industrial society, planted or mailed powerful bombs to unsuspecting innocent victims.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Murdering Cowboy
programme.desc: The sun set on the Wild West long ago, but some people refused to notice. Claude Dallas was one of them. A wily trapper, Dallas typified the rugged individualism that forged this country. He went too far when he killed two game wardens in 1981.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The World Trade Center Bombing
programme.desc: Terrorist bombings are what happen in other countries. Not here in the United States. And yet, in 1993, it happened in New York City.

programme.title: The FBI Files: John Gotti: Convicted
programme.desc: John Gotti was ambitious, powerful and ruthless. He ruled with flash and conspicuous style, playing celebrity with the media and cat and mouse with the FBI. They called John Gotti the Teflon Don. Serious charges just wouldn't stick.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The True Story of Mississippi Burning
programme.desc: Philadelphia, Mississippi, 1964. A sleepy southern town steeped in tradition finds itself targeted for invasion.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Model Killer
programme.desc: It's a model's job to rivet the public's attention. But in 1984, some aspiring models began attracting publicity in a terrible new way.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hired Gun
programme.desc: When three people were found murdered in their home, it appeared like a burglary gone awry. But a crime this horrific deserved a closer look.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cat and Mouse
programme.desc: He was a predator, abducting girls and young women from their own front yards in broad daylight. He was a sadist: phoning one victim's family, taunting them, boosting then dashing their hope, and he wouldn't stop until we stopped him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Cracking The Cartel
programme.desc: A mother and child are kidnapped, a bystander is murdered. Violence such as this shattered a quiet Texas neighborhood and exposed a drug cartel that flourished where it was least expected.

programme.title: The FBI Files: A Stranger in Town
programme.desc: She appeared on the highway in the spring, a young woman, her life cut short, her past and her identity a mystery. Only by finding out who she was could we ever hope to find her killer.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: The Festive Season Kicks Off
programme.desc: Durban, South Africa is a hot spot for vacationers during the busy summer season. The season starts on high alert when senior lifeguard Sihle rescues a bather caught in a rip current.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Busiest Day of the Year
programme.desc: New Year’s is the busiest day of the year in Durban. Crowds arrive in hopes that the sea, soft sand and sunshine will cure their hangovers. It's a day of frivolity and endless mishaps.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Powercraft
programme.desc: It's December 31 — a good day for lifeguard trainee Penny to face her fear of big waves. All eyes are on her as she paddles into some of the biggest waves of the season.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Mass Rescue
programme.desc: There's pandemonium at the Wedge when a flash rip sweeps 150 bathers — most of whom can’t swim — off of the sand bank and into deep, treacherous water.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: African Christmas
programme.desc: The fun and festivity of Christmas Day are put on hold after a mass blue bottle jellyfish attack. Lifeguards are forced to close Battery Beach and Country Club.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Day of Reconciliation
programme.desc: The Day of Reconciliation — the first big public holiday of the festive season — starts off damp and overcast. Undeterred, 150,000 vacationers flock to the beaches.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Shark Attack
programme.desc: Five bathers are bitten by an unknown sea creature at the Bay of Plenty, breaking the festive mood and creating a mass panic. Could this be a shark attack?

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Ragers Start the Party
programme.desc: High school graduates, or "ragers," spill onto Umhlanga Beach after partying all night. This beach is plagued by hidden rocks and strong rips — a disaster cocktail for party animals.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Most Dangerous Beach
programme.desc: Senior lifeguard Luthuli and his “men of steel” work the Wedge, Durban’s most dangerous beach. The shoreline has an unstable sand bank with dangerous holes on either side.

programme.title: Way of the Ocean: Australia
programme.desc: Way of the Ocean Australia explores the connection between man and sea through a visual feast of poetic motion. This wave rich continent provides a breathtaking backdrop to some of the best surfing found on the planet.

programme.title: Volcom Stone Presents: BS! (2014)
programme.desc: BS! is an out of the ordinary, if not extraordinary surf film that documents the serious ripping of Dusty Payne, Mitch Coleborn, Alex Gray, Ozzie Wright, Nate Tyler, and Andrew Doheny.

programme.title: Surfing Presents: Du Ciel
programme.desc: This stunning piece of cinema celebrates everything we love about the ocean, including its raw power and ability to put man in his place.

programme.title: Surfer Girlz - Heat Wave
programme.desc: Surfer Girlz Heat Wave interviews the world's best women surfers and even surfing legend Kelly Slater.

programme.title: Surf Skate
programme.desc: What does surfing and skating have in common? If you said, "sick airs" then you would be correct! Surf Skate - Above-the-Lip has plenty of mental surfing and skating airs.

programme.title: Surf Rider Single Fin
programme.desc: Witness some of the most stylish and smile filled rides ever. A classic longboard surf movie for all ages to enjoy. Filmed in high definition with both land and water angles.

programme.title: Surf One
programme.desc: Surf One explores the life and experiences of a tribe of surfers who search for the perfect wave and look to pass the stoke of surfing on to the younger generation.

programme.title: Stoked and Broke
programme.desc: A staycation Surfari Epic on Zero Dollar. Making their own boards, bamboo rickshaws, solar cookers, and hobo stoves, surfers Ryan Burch and Cyrus Sutton set off on a thirty mile, eight day walk through San Diego, CA.

programme.title: Shack Therapy
programme.desc: Shack up around the world as the crew explores South Africa, Hawaii, Norway, Mexico, Caroline Islands, and West Oz. Travel in Brian Conely's Hurricane Hunter to desolate Baja breaks.

programme.title: One California Day
programme.desc: Follow the lives of eight California surfers in One California Day. Produced by Build Worldwide, and Co-Directed by Mark Jeremias (maker of Drive) and Jason Baffa (maker of Singlefin Yellow).

programme.title: Children of the Wind
programme.desc: Children of the Wind tells the story of the Bonaire windsurfers, a group of native Caribbean kids, who under the mentorship of Elvis Martinus, founder of the Bonaire Aquaspeed windsurfing club, overcame insuperable odds.

programme.title: Chapters
programme.desc: Chapters is a collection of stories told by a world class group of surfers. The cast of eight was selected to balance and bridge the gap between loggers and high performance longboarders.

programme.title: Castles In the Sky
programme.desc: It begins with a dream. A vision seeded in your mind. But the next step is the one that counts. The first step. Onto the plane. Into the sky. From that moment on, the journey takes on a life of its own.

programme.title: Alternative Surf Craft
programme.desc: Alternative Surf Craft profiles the surfers on the edge of the sport. These surfers carve their own path riding unique and alternative surf craft.

programme.title: Absolute Mexico
programme.desc: Absolute Mexico The Directors Cut - includes bonus footage not included in the original release. See insane tube rides; interviews with top pro-surfers and gorgeous footage of one of the biggest days ever filmed at Puerto Escondido.

programme.title: Absolute Chile
programme.desc: In this follow-up to Absolute Mexico, director Joshua Pomer explores the northern coast of Chile. There we find an all-star crew heading south for some big wave tow surfing.

programme.title: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory
programme.desc: 1000 Waves to Surfing Glory is presented in a dream like structure with no distracting titles letting the visual imagery speak freely to your surfing soul and wanderlust.

programme.title: Chill: Cold Water Classic, Canada & World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia
programme.desc: Jarrad Howse takes Chill to the hidden surfing destination of Tofino in Canada. Cold, wet and windy but better yet, sublime surf! We catch up with the Pro's at the Cold Water Classic.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Women's Waterski Jumping, Australia & World Cup Waterski Slalom, Indonesia
programme.desc: This week on Chill, it's water skiing around the world, we're at the jumping in Australia and the slalom in Palembang. We check out PKRA Mexico, then catch up with surfing sensations, Courtney Cologue and Sage Erickson.

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Girls Pro, France & Kite Foil Gold Cup, Mexico
programme.desc: Chill heads to France to follow some of the biggest names in women's Surfing for a day of relaxation. An inside look at the technique needed to perform at the highest level in Kitesurfing. And we Chill with Japanese surf star Izuku Tanaka.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Indonesia & Longboard Pro Circuit, China
programme.desc: We look at the skills required and the thrills delivered by the wave that stands as the king of them all - the mighty Barrel. The Longboard Pro Circuit in China is our next destination where we hang out with Kassia Meador and Darcy Liu..

programme.title: Chill: Swatch Pro Tour, France & World Cup Waterski Jumping, Australia
programme.desc: Chill joins the girls of the Swatch Pro Tour in South West France, the top riders and local talent in the freestyle section of the PKRA event in Mexico and the men of world cup waterski jumping in Australia.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Italy
programme.desc: The very best in Women's wakeboarding as the IWWF comes to Mandurah in Australia. The beautiful Italian Island of Sicily plays host to the Kitesurfing world Tour.

programme.title: Chill: Action Sports Game, Australia & Women's World Longboard Championship, China
programme.desc: Chill heads down under for some water ski-jumping with the Men's Action Tricks Comp and Women's Ski Jump. We take an in-depth look at the Women's longboard Championships in the South China Sea.

programme.title: Chill: Waterski Jump Legend, Freddy Krueger & Women Longboard Professionals, China
programme.desc: This week we will travel to Western Australia to catch up with the Waterski Jump Legend Freddy Krueger. Style, elegance and a hard edge of competition combine in China as we watch some of the best women longboard professionals.

programme.title: Chill: World Kitesurfing Champion, Youri Zoon
programme.desc: Chill heads to Rio to follow some of the biggest names in the Surfing arena. An inside look with World Kitesurfing Champion Youri Zoon and an intimate training session with a bunch of Wakeboarders.

programme.title: Chill: Freddy Krueger, Wakeboard World Cup Australia
programme.desc: Freddy "The Nightmare" Krueger is the undisputed ski jumping legend. Chill gets up close and personal to discover his drive and passion which ultimately keeps him striving for perfection.

programme.title: Chill: World Cup Wakeboarding, Australia & Kitesurfing World Tour, Morocco
programme.desc: We are on the waters of Mandurah, Australia for the men's finals at the IWWF Wakeboard World. Morocco is our next destination for the kitesurf world tour, and we profile Harley Clifford.

programme.title: Minds in the Water
programme.desc: The story of one surfer's international journey to help protect dolphins, whales and their ocean environment. Shot on location in Australia, the Galapagos, Chile and Japan, it captures a key moment in one person's life when apathy is no longer an option.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Missing Person
programme.desc: Tragedy unfolds at Westbrook Beach when lifeguards are unable to locate a missing man. The man will be deemed lost at sea if he isn’t found soon, so senior lifeguard Ant takes charge.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers
programme.desc: The Burj Dubai holds the title as the tallest man-made structure ever built. Pushing the technological envelope. Near India's capital Delhi, the Qutub Minar reigns supreme for almost a thousand years as the world's tallest brick minaret.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers
programme.desc: On a an island the size of Singapore, water scarcity is a dire issue. The solution is the construction of an urban reservoir, the first of its kind in the world. Together with cutting edge technology, Singapore is on its way to water sufficiency.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 3
programme.desc: Tankers are the workhorses of our modern economy and the largest of these are built in Korea. Features like double-hulls and multiple tanks have pushed the cargo and safety capacity of tankers to new heights, making them the mainstay of the oil industry.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 4
programme.desc: For years, the roads of Mumbai were a hotbed of congestion and overcrowding. Now, a dynamic link road promises to ease the city's traffic woes. But the construction of Mumbai's first double-tiered flyover has been anything but easy.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 5
programme.desc: The largest airport terminal in the world in Beijing is an engineering marvel that nonetheless pays strict adherence to the principles of Chinese fengshui, and marks a new footnote in an age-old tradition of building big.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 6
programme.desc: It is the world's deepest immersed Tunnel. The Marmaray Project promises to ease Istanbul's decades-old traffic woes. Located in an earthquake zone, it is an engineer feat that is only rivalled by the discovery of a nearby ancient port.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 7
programme.desc: Self declared 8th Wonder of the World, the Palm trilogy are the largest man-made islands in the world. Employing technology like satellite positioning, it has broken new records and engineering milestones.

programme.title: Ingenuity - Engineering Ground Breakers: Episode 8
programme.desc: The Three Gorges Dam is the largest hydro-electric dam in the world. That it is a sheer engineering marvel cannot be denied. Yet questions abound over environmental and social issues, not to mention logistics problems of moving ships up and down river.

programme.title: Masters of Engineering
programme.desc: Which was the invention that propelled the construction of higher and higher buildings? Concrete? Iron? It's the elevator. From the Tower of Babel to the Kingdom Tower in Saudi Arabia, humankind has always searched to build bigger and higher.

programme.title: Masters of Engineering
programme.desc: 70% of the earth's surface is covered by water and much of the history of man's discovery of the earth is linked to oceans. From the fragile boats which sailed along the Mediterranean coasts to the majestic ships which sailed off to the New World.

programme.title: Masters of Engineering
programme.desc: How are gravity defying bridges designed? For centuries there have been countless and huge advances in the field of civil engineering. Thanks to the explanations of leading, the viewer plunges into a world of inventions.

programme.title: Masters of Engineering
programme.desc: To fly... A dream that has shaped the history of humanity. A story of crazy flyers - inventors, scientists - pursuing their dream, often risking their lives doing so. Matthieu Barreau went in search of these intrepid pioneers.

programme.title: Masters of Engineering
programme.desc: For centuries there have been countless and huge advances in the field of civil engineering. Thanks to the explanations of leading experts in physics, maths and other hard sciences. In this film we look at the masters of rail.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Creator
programme.desc: Creating is a deed that captivates minds. Today, we are better creators than ever before. We will see how we can play with conditions for creating life, make anything we can think of with the code of life itself, and replace parts of our body.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Conqueror
programme.desc: Humankind conquered the world, in order to survive, and conquers his fellow humans with new ideas. We will see how we as a species have conquered the earth, how we still compete with viruses, and how quantum theory conquers China.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Maker
programme.desc: The maker grasps humankind as builders. We make new constructions with building blocks from nature, which we manipulate at the same time. We will see how that leads us to new materials, new connections between people and new bursts of creativity.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Explorer
programme.desc: The explorer peers beyond our known borders and discloses the unknown. We will get a glimpse of the secrets of life, both on earth and elsewhere in the universe, and zoom in on the peculiar history of our own planet. What are the borders yet to cross?

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Illusionist
programme.desc: As humans, we construct our view of reality from the input provided by our senses. How does that work? And how can we make a robot experience something similar? What would the world be like with human minds and artificial ones living together?

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Dreamer
programme.desc: It is through our wildest dreams that we achieve new knowledge. We see dreams of feeding the world with insects, dreams of a synthesis of the fundamental theories of physics, and dreams of our future as extra-terrestrials.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Searcher
programme.desc: We keep expanding our knowledge, and sometimes we know exactly what we are looking for. Patterns in apparent chaos, new elements or a key for translating old and forgotten languages. We are sure they exist.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Player
programme.desc: Humans and animals play and this renders them familiar with their environments. We zoom in on scientists who combine play and mathematics, and see how playing with matter yields new materials with special properties.

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Thinker
programme.desc: Our brains are constantly aware of our place in reality. How does this work for animals? Does an objective reality even exist, and does it leave any room for something like god? Where will our thinking lead us?

programme.title: Mind of the Universe: The Connector
programme.desc: Humankind, society and technology are dramatically influenced by science. In this episode we connect all the knowledge of The Mind of the Universe in an overarching outlook on the future. What is the future of humanity, society, and knowledge?

programme.title: What If

programme.desc: Before we can reach space, we must first be able to see it. Hundreds of years ago, the simple telescope was used to give us a seemingly closer vantage. Today, we use the awe-inspiring, and super powerful, Hubble Space Telescope.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Superscopes
programme.desc: The human eye can only see visible light, a small spectrum of electromagnetic waves. Today, we have instruments that let us perceive all wavelengths.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Virtual Universe
programme.desc: Our understanding of the cosmos is limited by the amount of time we have to see it. Fortunately, computer simulations can help us see how galaxies interact over millions of years, and even how dark matter structures the universe.

programme.desc: Gravity has long been a force that has intrigued scientists. Now, for the first time scientists are probing to detect gravity waves in space as well as mapping the gravity patterns of the moon.

programme.desc: Meet owner Paul Brown and the team of Gallery 63 as they prepare for their next auction. Paul verifies a 19th-century vampire killing kit with more than 30 items to kill the monster.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A seller brings in an ancient hand cannon so rare, the experts have a hard time figuring out what exactly it is. Owner Paul discovers a treasure in a seller's mish-mash box of stuff: a unique jeweled, gold-encased Faberge pencil on a chain.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Half the fun of an item is the reason of why someone is willing to sell it. This week on Auction Kings, a rockabilly musician cruises in with a gleaming Pink 1960 Cadillac.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: At an auction, sometimes the seller gets the deal, and sometimes the buyer does. This week on Auction Kings, a collector brings in a pair of 19th-century ladies pistols that were designed to be concealed in a hand muff.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul and the Gallery 63 team get a lesson in the celebrity factor when a seller brings in a snooker table (similar to an American pool table) that was commissioned and toured with the Rolling Stones.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Auctions are a risky business. Sometimes seemingly worthless items sell big and fabulous items fall flat. This week on Auction Kings, Cindy teaches Jon how to tell what will sell.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: All items have a story, and it can make or break their sale at auction. This week on Auction Kings, Cindy takes in two chairs that may have come from a New Orleans cathouse.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Handyman Delfino's skills are put to the test in repairing a Love Meter game. Once repaired, the team has some friendly competition to see who is Gallery 63's best lover.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Manager Cindy's new stress releaser, a new drum set Jon brought in on a pick, is stressing everyone else out. Owner Paul can't be rid of the auction item fast enough.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Owner Paul Brown and the Gallery 63 team prepare for their next auction, which includes a Woolly Mammoth tusk and a giant, unset sapphire. Manager Cindy faces her fears and gets the ride of her life when she and Paul go up in a hot air balloon.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Owner Paul Brown and the Gallery 63 team prepare for their next auction, which includes a 1908 Louis Vuitton steamer trunk and a samurai sword. Picker Jon passes the test when he brings back and mends an antique desk complete with secret compartments.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week, a seller comes in with a fabulous, 1969 Vespa with a sidecar. A frightening headhunter’s axe finds its way into the gallery, and Paul and Cindy fight over a vintage Coca Cola machine – along with a slew of bidders who also want it!

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week, Paul takes chances on three items that aren’t sure things. A trading knife that could be made by the famous Hudson Bay Trading Co., an antique wooden chest that a seller wants an unattainable $75,000 and a Johnny Cash signed guitar.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week on Auction Kings, Paul encourages his son Elijah to learn more about the family business challenging him to sell an item of his own at the upcoming auction.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week at Gallery 63, a large, ornate European cabinet and a tiny European hand mirror signed by Napoleon both appear at Gallery 63 along with a WWI Boy Scout War Bonds Poster – a true piece of original Americana.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A 1940’s bicycle with a motor along with a vintage slot machine and a pinball machine like the one seen on “Happy Days” are auctioned off, a WW2 battlefield Russian flag gets tested, while Paul gets put on Cindy’s “Wall of Shame”.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week at Gallery 63, items from World War II tug at everyone’s heartstrings, and a Ouija Board gives Cindy the creeps. A 1947 Rock-ola Jukebox, beautifully restored by the owner and a 1946 Willys Jeep perfectly restored by Richard Petty.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: This week at Gallery 63, sellers part with an enormous box of antique iron figurine toys, a homemade scrapbook chronicling Charles Lindbergh’s transatlantic flight complete with a Lindbergh signature and a 1922 Wurlitzer Band Organ.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: An autographed edition of Magaret Mitchell’s Gone with the Wind has all the makings of being the real deal; Cindy and Delfino receive petrified dinosaur dung to sell; and Paul travels to an ancient spring where he gets a 5,000 year old pipe for auction.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul finds two babies, the earliest version of the Cabbage Patch dolls at a seller’s home – signed by their creator, Xavier Roberts. Jon researches a poem written and signed by Jim Morrison to try to authenticate it.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul puts a 3-carat diamond ring on the block; a nautical collector auctions a vintage diving helmet and a ship’s binnacle; and a bull sack signed by rodeo great Ty Murray generates a lot of excitement at Gallery 63.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul discovers if it’s legal to sell an authentic Appalachian Moonshine Still; a decrepit pair of Iron Knuckles and a beat-up Infantry Button could prove to be rusty relics from the Civil War.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A huge, high-quality taxidermy collection comes in with a $20,000 asking price; a seller consigns a vintage novelty scale that tells your weight – and your fortune; and a collector brings in a tin of baseball cards dating back to the 1930s.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: On the block this week at Gallery 63 – an American flag guitar signed by Bruce Springsteen; a collectible Cadillac first owned by Elvis Presley; and some rare family heirlooms – handwritten notes from Thomas Edison.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: The 1980s are back with a vengeance at Gallery 63 – a suped-up 1982 Corvette convertible rolls in; a Beverly Hills High School grad drops off her old ‘80s yearbooks, packed with celebrities.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A seller brings an antique signal cannon to Gallery 63 and Paul fires it off; a woman hopes to sell a cabinet that she says is haunted by a friendly ghost; and a pilot hopes to get $30,000 for his Grumman airplane.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: An exact replica of the Back to the Future DeLorean Time Machine has the potential to be the biggest sale in Gallery 63’s history; an early 20th Century piano surprises everyone with a speakeasy-style bar inside.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: The U.S. Space and Rocket Center raises money for Space Camp scholarships by auctioning off – a Vintage Racecar; an Apollo 13 Pinball Machine owned by actor Bill Paxton; and 2 rare Soviet Spacesuits that have actually been in space!

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul’s father Bob auctions a 19th Century gambler’s watch that has a concealed firearm attached; Paul sells an eye-popping 1943 Harley Flathead; and a seller mails in a rusty old tobacco tin that might just be the most valuable item of all!

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul takes in a classic 1965 Mustang muscle car; a father-daughter team brings in set of super-retro Vintage Lunchboxes; and a man attempts to save his relationship by selling his Stumpf Fiddle, a whacky, noisy percussion instrument.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Sellers bring in a collection of letters, diaries, and documents chronicling their ancestor’s life as a Civil War infantry captain; a collector brings in a functioning 19th Century camera, and a man brings in a telescope.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A personal letter written by legendary magician Harry Houdini is evaluated by Houdini’s nephew; an eye-popping 1951 Ford F-1 pickup truck rolls in with some problems under the surface.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: Paul is thrilled to get a rare 1920s Cigar Boy lighter; Jon is excited when he comes back from a pick with a 400-year-old desk; and a seller brings in a letter written to her father by Albert Einstein.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: A handmade Gaming Table – complete with surfaces for cards, checkers, chess, backgammon and roulette; a vintage British Rocking Horse that seems fit for a young prince; and a 1947 Servi-Car – a 3-wheeled motorcycle that’s as unique as it is cool.

programme.title: Auction Kings
programme.desc: The crew is captivated by a mysterious device that grabs and pulls your fingers; Paul takes in the smallest sword he’s ever seen; and the Gallery gets filled up with a giant model railroad layout.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 8 Chefs Compete
programme.desc: The teams must create an ethnic dish in 45 minutes including a protein of their choice. The winners go on a shopping spree at a boutique and receive a set of copper-clad cookware.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 7 Chefs Compete (Part One)
programme.desc: The remaining chefs participate in a challenge that tests their skills at identifying foods merely by touch. The winners eat seafood at Malibu's Nobu restaurant.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 7 Chefs Compete (Part Two)
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay rewards the chef who has made the greatest stride in the competition with immunity from elimination during the next dinner service, in which the contestants try to impress the judges.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: An all new set of contestants tries to impress Chef Gordon Ramsay with their culinary skills in order to win the coveted position of head chef at New York City's BLT Steak restaurant.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The remaining chefs try to rebound from their disastrous first dinner service. Their challenge this episode? Preparing New York steak strips, rib eyes, filets and burgers.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: In this episode, the remaining contestants receive a wakeup call from clowns. They must prepare pasta and quesadillas for fifty kids and panini sandwiches for their moms.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay gives the contestants a chicken challenge that includes catching live fowl. The winners spend a day riding in go-karts while the losers prepare chickens for the next service.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The remaining chefs get a demonstration in dessert preparation using sound waves and liquid nitrogen, then must steam, poach or boil protein-based dishes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The contestants prepare Hawaiian dishes for a high school's twentieth reunion. The winners spend the day on a yacht while the losers transform Hell's Kitchen to look Hawaiian.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The chefs prepare five dishes that must include at least one type of beer. The winners attend the Long Beach Grand Prix IndyCar race while the losers unload kegs of beer and bags of ice.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The ten budding chefs prepare comfort foods, with Wolfgang Puck judging them. The winners attend a show at L.A.'s Laugh Factory and take a ride in a convertible, while the losers have to clean the dorms.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: Contestants need to be at their sweetest when Chef Ramsay gives them a dessert challenge. The winning team flies to Sin City while the losers prep the kitchen for Hell's Kitchen's "Date Night.”.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The remaining chefs are put to a blind taste test. The winners ride horses in the Hollywood Hills while the losers peel grapes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The seven remaining competitors visit New York City, where they tour BLT Steak. When they return to Hell's Kitchen, their challenge is to prepare ethnic dishes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The teams must prepare three dishes. The catch? One must be made in thirty minutes, one in twenty and the last in only ten minutes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: For the first time in "Hell's Kitchen" history, chefs from prior seasons return to compete with the remaining competitors.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: In this episode's challenge, each chef must create something special from Alaskan salmon. The winner gets a helicopter ride and lunch at LA's Water Grill. The losers prep fish for the dinner service.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The final four chefs eat a dish prepared by Chef Ramsay. For their challenge, they must recreate it in 35 minutes. The winner goes to a baseball game while the losers move furniture out of the dorms.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: While wearing new white dinner jackets, the final contestants prepare a menu consisting of four appetizers, four entrees and three desserts.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: Eighteen chefs vie for a head chef position at Gordon Ramsay Steak at the Paris Las Vegas hotel and casino. Ramsay splits up the contestants into two teams.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The chefs remove scallops from a mound of ice and seaweed before cooking them to Chef Ramsay's standards. The first team to make six plates of five scallops wins a day of yacht cruising.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The two teams must cook a meal for sixty newly naturalized U.S. citizens. The winners go on a safari trip in San Diego while the losers do manual labor at the Ballona Wetlands.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The aspiring chefs create four different lamb dishes. The winners spend a day at the horse races while the losers first wash paint off the sheep, then clean the kitchens for the dinner service.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: Fashion and food mix when the contestants prepare an haute couture-inspired menu for designers. The winners get new wardrobes while the losers prepare a dinner service.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 6 Chefs Compete
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay tests the remaining contestants' abilities to communicate with one another in a three-entrée relay race. The winners tour Los Angeles by helicopter and visit the King Gillette Ranch to sample caviar.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 5 Chefs Compete (Part One)
programme.desc: Each chef has 45 minutes to use a pressure cooker to make a meal using one of five cheap cuts of meat — each hidden in a pressure cooker — and fashion the dish as a five-star entrée.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 5 Chefs Compete (Part Two)
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay devises a team of former "Hell's Kitchen" winners to challenge the remaining contestants. The two teams must wow Chef Ramsay with their signature dishes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 5 Chefs Compete (Part Three)
programme.desc: The budding chefs create ten gourmet burgers, which are then evaluated by Chef Ramsay, Jean-Philippe and a row of judges associated with some of the finest restaurants in the country.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: 2 Chefs Compete
programme.desc: The final two chefs must prepare two appetizers and three entrées to present to a panel of respected judges. The winner gets first pick in drafting a team comprised of chefs eliminated from the competition prior to the finale.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen: Winner Chosen
programme.desc: In the season finale, the two chefs and their respective teams participate in a final dinner service that will determine this season's winner.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The runway show dinner proves distracting for some, while other contestants succeed despite the pressure to time the service perfectly with the show.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: For the dinner service, the remaining contestants must serve Tito Ortiz and Sugar Ray Leonard protein-packed dishes that'll knock their socks off.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The contestants must prepare a thirty-minute meal in which a slot machine randomly determines the ingredients that they can use. The winners go on a shopping spree for kitchenware and utensils.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The chefs continue to compete at Gordon Ramsay Steak at the Paris Las Vegas Hotel & Casino, but personal conflicts distract from their work.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: For this episode's challenge, all of the chefs roll a twelve-sided dice to determine their ingredients. Each team produces one dish using all the ingredients named.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The teams submit to the annual blind taste test challenge. The winners spend a day at a water park while the losers make deliveries, grind peppercorn, change the oil in the fryers and peel potatoes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The remaining chefs create their own menus in the toughest challenge yet. Chef Ramsay relies on diner comment cards for his brutally honest criticism.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: A Southern gospel choir sings a rendition of "This Little Light of Mine" to the remaining contestants. The teams must put a modern spin on a traditional southern dish in thirty minutes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The two teams must prepare three dishes from the regular Hell's Kitchen menu in a tag-team race. Chef Ramsay judges the dishes on completeness, appearance and taste.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The contestants taste Chef Lefebvre and Chef Hatfield's dishes. This leads to a challenge in which the chefs must distinguish the ingredients in the meals and reproduce it in thirty minutes.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: The chefs must teach five Miss Teen USA winners how to cook a chicken parmesan dish using only words for guidance. The winner enjoys a gourmet Italian lunch and kayaking in the Venice canals.

programme.title: Hell's Kitchen
programme.desc: For today's challenge, the chefs take a trip to Bristol Farms supermarket and have ten minutes to spend fifteen dollars on ingredients. The chefs must cook a dish with the groceries they bought.

programme.title: Drakensberg - Africa's Dragon Mountain
programme.desc: A dragon hatched from the volcanic furnaces of Gondwanaland. Ancient almost beyond comprehension, yet a living thing. And vast, stretching across a subcontinent, its spine arching above the clouds...

programme.title: Aerial Spain
programme.desc: This time, we take a tour through inland Spain. It’s a dream-like landscape full of villages, rivers, mountains, and valleys. Travel down warm coastlines, leafy valleys, rivers, mountains that hide charming villages still harboring their traditions.

programme.title: Way of the Ocean: Australia
programme.desc: Way of the Ocean Australia explores the connection between man and sea through a visual feast of poetic motion. This wave rich continent provides a breathtaking backdrop to some of the best surfing found on the planet.

programme.title: Aerial Odyssey: Germany From Above
